principatu civium. Prof. Robinson Ellis notices the significance of these words. In order to make his principatus less offensive, Tiberius pretended to be civilis, i.e. on a level with ordinary Roman citizens. Hence civium tones down principatus in accord- ance with this affectation of Tiberius.
